            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:third-party-content">
              <strong class="block mb-2">B. Third-Party Content and Trademarks:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:5me7mj">Certain names, logos, and materials displayed on the platform may constitute the intellectual property of third parties, including our portfolio companies, ecosystem partners, or regulatory bodies. The use of such third-party content is strictly for identification and informational purposes under fair use provisions. Nothing on this platform should be construed as granting any license or right to use any trademark displayed without the written permission of the respective owner.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:user-submissions-ip">
              <strong class="block mb-2">C. User Submissions and Independent Development:</strong>
              <p class="mb-4" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:5me7mi">We respect the intellectual property of our Ideapreneurs, Solopreneurs, and business partners. You retain the intellectual property rights to any pitch decks, business plans, or proprietary data you submit to SPVH via "The First Cheque" program or other contact portals.</p>
              <p class="mb-4" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:5me7mh">However, by submitting such materials, you grant SPVH a limited, internal license to review, evaluate, and retain the documents for investment consideration and compliance purposes. You acknowledge that SPVH operates as an active investment holding group that continuously reviews, evaluates, and invests in a large volume of diverse business models. SPVH may currently be evaluating, or may in the future independently develop, fund, or collaborate with, businesses that are competitive with, or conceptually similar to, your submission.</p>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:5me7lv">You agree that the submission of your materials does not create a fiduciary relationship, a binding Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA), or any obligation of exclusivity. SPVH shall not be held liable for any claims of intellectual property misappropriation or breach of confidentiality arising solely from the independent development or funding of similar concepts, provided SPVH has not directly utilized your copyrighted materials or patented technology without authorization.</p>
            </div>
