            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:cap-liability">
              <strong class="block mb-2">D. Cap on Liability:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:5me7lm">In no event shall SPVH's total aggregate liability to you for all claims, damages, losses, and causes of action (whether in contract, tort, negligence, or otherwise) arising out of or relating to your use of the platform exceed the amount paid by you, if any, for accessing this website, or Indian Rupees Ten Thousand (INR 10,000), whichever is lesser.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:risk-ack">
              <strong class="block mb-2">E. Risk Acknowledgment:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8u">You acknowledge that participating in early-stage venture capital, seeking investments, and interacting with holding companies involves inherent business risks. You assume full responsibility and risk for your use of the platform and your interactions with SPVH.</p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="mt-12" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:xtpw2r">
            <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:tjkaw3">6. Governing Law</h2>
            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:governing-law">
              <strong class="block mb-2">A. Governing Law:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8t">These Terms of Service, along with any separate agreements whereby we provide you services or evaluate your submissions, shall be governed by, construed, and enforced in accordance with the laws of the Republic of India, without regard to its conflict of law principles.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:exclusive-jurisdiction">
              <strong class="block mb-2">B. Exclusive Jurisdiction:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8s">Subject to the arbitration provisions set forth below, you explicitly and irrevocably consent to the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the competent courts located in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India, for the adjudication of any disputes or claims arising out of or relating to your use of the platform.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dispute-resolution">
              <strong class="block mb-2">C. Dispute Resolution (Arbitration):</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8r">Any dispute, controversy, or claim arising out of or relating to these Terms, the breach thereof, or the platform's usage, shall be settled by binding arbitration in accordance with the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, and its subsequent amendments. The arbitration shall be conducted by a sole arbitrator mutually appointed by both parties. The seat and venue of the arbitration shall be Mumbai, Maharashtra. All proceedings shall be conducted, and the award shall be rendered, in the English language. The arbitral award shall be final and binding upon both parties.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:equitable-relief">
              <strong class="block mb-2">D. Equitable Relief:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8q">Notwithstanding the agreement to arbitrate in Section 6(C), you acknowledge that any breach of our intellectual property rights, system security, or unauthorized data extraction may cause irreparable harm to SPVH Private Limited for which monetary damages would be inadequate. Therefore, SPVH expressly retains the right to seek immediate injunctive relief, specific performance, or other equitable remedies in any court of competent jurisdiction without the necessity of posting a bond or waiting for arbitration proceedings to commence or conclude.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:severability">
              <strong class="block mb-2">E. Severability:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8p">If any provision of these Terms is found by a court or arbitrator of competent jurisdiction to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.</p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="mt-12" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:access-availability">
            <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:access-title">7. Access & Availability</h2>
            <div class="mb-6" data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:right-modify">
              <strong class="block mb-2">A. Right to Modify or Withdraw:</strong>
              <p data-ps="src/pages/terms-of-service.astro:dxgc8o">SPVH Private Limited reserves the absolute right to withdraw, amend, suspend, or discontinue the platform, any of its affiliated portals, or any service or material we provide on the platform, at our sole discretion and without prior notice. We will not be liable if, for any reason, all or any part of the platform is unavailable at any time or for any period.</p>
